{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}} {{refimprove|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox video game | title = Badland 2 | image = The logo of Badland 2.png | caption = [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]] icon | developer = [[Frogmind Games]] | publisher = Cheetah Games | series = ''Badland'' | platforms = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | released = '''iOS''' 17 December 2015 '''Android''' 8 September 2016 | genre = [[Puzzle video game|Puzzle]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] }}
'''''Badland 2''''' (stylized '''''BADLAND 2''''') is a [[mobile video game]] designed by Frogmind Games and released on the [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] platforms. The game was released on 17 December 2015 on iOS and 8 September 2016 on Android. It is the sequel of ''[[Badland (video game)|Badland]]''.<ref name=frogmind>{{cite web|title=Badland 2 arrives on Android|url=http://frogmind.com/badland-2-arrives-to-android/|website=frogmind.com|publisher=Frogmind|date=8 September 2016|accessdate=2 October 2016}}</ref><ref name=phonearena> {{cite web|title=Badland 2 gets a surprise release on iOS|url=http://www.phonearena.com/news/Badland-2-gets-a-surprise-release-on-iOS_id76792|website=Phonearena.com|publisher=Phonearena|date=18 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015}}</ref>
==Development== The game was unveiled by Juhana Myllys, the co-founder and lead designer of the Frogmind Games, who said that the game was the company's attempt to reinvent the first ''Badland'', where they wanted the game to be worthy of the word ''sequel''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Badland 2 is Available For iOS As of Today|url=http://wegotthiscovered.com/gaming/badland-2-ios/|date=18 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015|website=Wegotthiscovered.com|publisher=We Got This Covered}}</ref>
==Gameplay== Similar to the first game, the player flies around a little black creature through the woods of the game. Beginning in Day 1 Dawn, the game progresses through four stages (Dawn, Noon, Dusk, and Night), each with a separate color scheme and new theme of traps. But unlike in the first game, the game features new tactics such as flying in both directions, new obstacles such as water, liquids, flamethrower, frost, magma and searing light.<ref>{{cite web|title=Frogmind's Badland 2 is the side-scrolling sequel to a 30M download hit|url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/12/17/frogminds-badland-2-is-the-side-scrolling-sequel-to-30m-download-hit/|date=17 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015|website=venturebeat.com|publisher=VentureBeat}}</ref> The game also features new mode which makes the creature into a rolling wheel.<ref>{{cite web|title=Moody mobile game Badland has a fantastic new sequel|url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/12/17/10298232/badland-2-iphone-ipad|website=theverge.com|publisher=The Verge|date=17 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015}}</ref> The game also offers standalone challenges stages for the player to compete against their friends via the online leaderboard.<ref>{{cite web|title=Badland 2 out now on iOS|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-12-17-badland-2-is-out-now-on-ios|date=17 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015|website=eurogamer.net|publisher=Euro Gamer}}</ref> The new version of game also included 3 different modes; survive the longest, save the most clones or reach the end fastest.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.slashgear.com/badland-2-released-with-neat-3d-touch-features-for-iphone-6s-17418979/|title=BADLAND 2 released with neat 3D Touch features for iPhone 6S|date=2015-12-17|work=SlashGear|access-date=2018-11-19|language=en-US}}</ref>
